The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Business Briefs
                                                                                                               Business Briefs
                              
	 New Delhi, June 18: Road transport and highways minister Kamal Nath today said the government had set a target of building 7,000km of roads in a year. The estimated cost for building each kilometre will be Rs 6 crore. The total expenditure is envisaged at Rs 42,000 crore per annum for the next five years.                            
	 Washington, June 18: The US has given General Electric India the validated end-user status, which will enable it to receive certain controlled US technology items without an individual licence. US commerce secretary Gary Locke said it would facilitate the flow of trade between the nations.                            
	 New Delhi, June 18: Air India and no-frill carrier SpiceJet have increased the fuel surcharge per air ticket by Rs 400. While SpiceJet increased the surcharge with immediate effect, Air India said the hike would be effective from tomorrow.                             
	 Bangalore, June 18: LG Electronics plans to double its annual R amp;D investment in India to Rs 400 crore as it steps up its study on market dynamics and consumer behaviour to push sales.                            
	 Calcutta, June 18: DTH service provider Dish TV has reduced its net loss to Rs 78.66 crore in the fourth quarter ended March 31 from Rs 115.06 crore in the same period last year.                                                                                                                           
